President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Catherine Lhamon for the position of Assistant Secretary for Civil Rights at the Department of Education. Lhamon currently serves as the Deputy Assistant to the President and Deputy Director of the Domestic Policy Council for Racial Justice and Equity, where she oversees the President's equity policy portfolio. She previously chaired the U.S. Commission on Civil Rights and served as the Legal Affairs Secretary to California Governor Gavin Newsom. Lhamon has also worked as the Assistant Secretary for Civil Rights at the Department of Education under President Obama. She has a background in litigating civil rights cases and has taught federal civil rights appeals at Georgetown University Law Center. Lhamon is a graduate of Amherst College and Yale Law School.